name: help
description: Show the help menu with all commands or a specific command.

name: information
description: Get information about the bot.

name: invite
description: Get the invite link and support server link for the bot.

name: link
description: Link your Hypixel account to the bot.

name: unlink
description: Unlink your account from the bot.

name: vote
description: Get links to upvote the bot.

name: slayer
description: Get a player's slayer data.

name: calcslayer
description: Calculate the number of slayer bosses needed to reach a certain level or xp amount.

name: skills
description: Get a player's skill data.

name: hotm
description: Get a player's heart of the mountain statistics.

name: forge
description: Get a player's forge items and ending times.

name: crimson
description: Get a player's crimson isle statistics.

name: dungeons
description: Get a player's dungeon data.

name: essence
description: Main essence command.

subcommands.name: upgrade
subcommands.description: Interactive message to calculate the amount of essence and items to upgrade an item.

subcommands.name: information
subcommands.description: Get the amount of essence and items to upgrade an item for each level.

subcommands.name: player
subcommands.description: Get a player's essence amounts and essence shop upgrades.

name: calcruns
description: Calculate the number of runs needed to reach a certain catacombs level.

name: calcdrops
description: Calculate the drop rate and cost of all chests for a dungeons floor or for an item.

name: guild
description: Main guild command

subcommands.name: information
subcommands.description: Get information and statistics about a guild.

subcommands.name: members
subcommands.description: List all members in a guild.

subcommands.name: experience
subcommands.description: Get the experience leaderboard for a guild. Defaults to seven days.

subcommands.name: leaderboard
subcommands.description: Get a leaderboard for a guild.

subcommands.name: kicker
subcommands.description: Get all player's who don't meet the provided requirements. Requirements are in the format `[type:value ...] ...`. The requirement type can be skills, slayer, catacombs, weight, or level. The requirement value must be an integer. Requirements inside the brackets require at least one to be met, while outside require all to be met.

subcommands.name: top
subcommands.description: Get a guild's average and top 5 leaderboards of slayer, skills, catacombs, weight, networth, and level.

subcommands.name: check
subcommands.description: A customizable helper that will tell you who to kick, promote or demote in your Hypixel guild based on numerical requirements. Please join the [Skyblock Plus Discord](https://discord.gg/Z4Fn3eNDXT) and mention CrypticPlasma to setup this for your guild.

name: guildlb
description: Get a global guild leaderboard.

name: auctions
description: Get and/or track a player's unclaimed auctions on all profiles. Set verbose to true to show an estimated price breakdown for each auction.

name: viewauction
description: Get information about an auction by it's UUID.

name: bin
description: Get the lowest bin of an item.

name: attributes
description: Get the lowest priced attribute combination for an item.
examples: bin Aurora Boots Mana Pool Mana Regeneration

name: bazaar
description: Get the bazaar prices of an item.

name: average
description: Get the average auction and bin price of an item.

name: bids
description: Get a player's auction house bids

name: price
description: Query the auction house for the lowest prices of an item. Allows for more specific queries than bin or average command. Defaults to searching auctions and bins.

name: bits
description: Get the coins to bits ratio for items in the bits shop.

name: copper
description: Get the coins to copper ratio for items in the SkyMart shop.

name: flips
description: Get current auction flips (**experimental**).

name: inventory
description: Main inventory command.

subcommands.name: emoji
subcommands.description: Get a player's inventory represented in emojis.

subcommands.name: list
subcommands.description: Get a player's inventory with lore.

name: museum
description: Main museum command.

subcommands.name: view
subcommands.description: View a player's museum items.

subcommands.name: cheapest
subcommands.description: Get the cheapest items to donate to a player's museum.

name: armor
description: Main armor command.

subcommands.name: emoji
subcommands.description: Get a player's armor and equipment represented in emojis.

subcommands.name: list
subcommands.description: Get a player's armor and equipment with lore.

name: enderchest
description: Main enderchest command.

subcommands.name: emoji
subcommands.description: Get a player's enderchest represented in emojis.

subcommands.name: list
subcommands.description: Get a player's enderchest with lore.

name: storage
description: Get a player's storage represented in emojis.

name: talisman
description: Main talisman command.

subcommands.name: emoji
subcommands.description: Get a player's talisman bag represented in emojis.

subcommands.name: list
subcommands.description: Get a player's talisman bag with lore.

subcommands.name: tuning
subcommands.description: Get a player's power stone stats and tuning stats

name: sacks
description: Get a player's sacks content bag represented in a list and sorted by descending price. Costs can be calculated from (source) bazaar only, npc only, or npc and bazaar.

name: wardrobe
description: Main wardrobe command.

subcommands.name: emoji
subcommands.description: Get a player's wardrobe represented in emojis.

subcommands.name: list
subcommands.description: Get a player's wardrobe with lore.

name: pets
description: Get a player's pets and missing pets.

name: roles
description: Main roles command.

subcommands.name: claim
subcommands.description: Claim your automatic Skyblock roles. You must be linked to the bot.

subcommands.name: list
subcommands.description: List all claimable roles for this server.

name: coins
description: Get a player's coins and bank history.

name: networth
description: Calculate a player's networth. Set verbose to true to get a detailed breakdown of the calculations.

name: weight
description: Get a player's slayer, skills, dungeons, and total weight. Shows both Senither and Lily weight.

name: calcweight
description: Calculate predicted weight change for a reaching a skills, slayers, or dungeons level/amount.

name: hypixel
description: Get Hypixel information about a player.

name: missing
description: Get a player's missing talismans and cheapest ones to buy.

name: checkapi
description: Get a player's enabled and disabled Skyblock APIs

name: cakes
description: Get a player's active and inactive cake buffs.

name: bestiary
description: Get a player's bestiary statistics.

name: harp
description: Get a player's harp statistics.

name: checkreqs
description: Check if a player meets any of the setup automated guild requirements.

name: uuid
description: Convert username to UUID or UUID to username.

name: fetchur
description: Get today's fetchur item.

name: level
description: Get a player's skyblock level.

name: collections
description: Get a player's collections.

name: jacob
description: Get the upcoming contests and their crops.

name: mayor
description: Get the current mayor and their perks.

name: leaderboard
description: Get a global leaderboard.

name: serverlb
description: Get a leaderboard for this server.

name: skyblock
description: Get an overview of a player's Skyblock profiles

name: bingo
description: Get the current bingo goals and a player's live bingo card.

name: recipe
description: Get the crafting recipe of an item.

name: craft
description: Calculate the cost of an item and added upgrades.

name: calendar
description: Get the current Skyblock datetime and running or upcoming events

name: scammer
description: Check if a player is marked as a scammer in the SkyblockZ database with the reason, Discords, and Minecraft alts

name: calcdrags
description: Calculate your loot quality and predicted loot from dragons in the end. The ratio is your damage divided by first place damage.

name: reforge
description: Get the reforge stone stats for each rarity.

name: party
description: Main party command.

subcommands.name: create
subcommands.description: Interactive message to create a new party.

subcommands.name: current
subcommands.description: Get information about your current party.

subcommands.name: join
subcommands.description: Join a player's party by the party leader's IGN.

subcommands.name: leave
subcommands.description: Leave your current party.

subcommands.name: list
subcommands.description: List all active parties

subcommands.name: disband
subcommands.description: Disband your current party.

subcommands.name: kick
subcommands.description: Kick a member from your party

name: event
description: Main event command.

subcommands.name: create
subcommands.description: Interactive message to create a Skyblock event.

subcommands.name: current
subcommands.description: Get information about the current event.

subcommands.name: join
subcommands.description: Join the current event.

subcommands.name: add
subcommands.description: Force add a player to the current event.

subcommands.name: leave
subcommands.description: Leave the current event.

subcommands.name: remove
subcommands.description: Force remove a player from the current event.

subcommands.name: leaderboard
subcommands.description: Get the leaderboard for current event.

subcommands.name: end
subcommands.description: Force end the event. If silent is true, the event will be canceled and no prizes or winners will be announced.

name: settings
description: Main settings command.

subcommands.name: general
subcommands.description: View general settings for this server.

subcommands.name: reset
subcommands.description: Clear and reset the current server settings.

subcommands.name: set
subcommands.description: Set certain settings.

subcommands.name: fetchur_channel
subcommands.description: Set the channel where fetchur notifications will be posted at 12 am EST every day.

subcommands.name: fetchur_ping
subcommands.description: Set the role that will be pinged with the daily fetchur notifications.

subcommands.name: mayor_channel
subcommands.description: Set the channel where notifications will be sent when a new mayor is elected or perks rotate.

subcommands.name: mayor_ping
subcommands.description: Set the role that will be pinged with mayor notifications.

subcommands.name: guest_role
subcommands.description: Set the role that will be given to linked users that are not in any of the setup automatic guilds. Requires at least one automatic guild to be setup.

subcommands.name: sync_unlinked
subcommands.description: Enable or disable whether unlinked members should also be synced for verified roles, automatic roles, and guild roles during automatic updates.

subcommands.name: bot_manager
subcommands.description: Manage bot manager roles.

subcommands.name: add
subcommands.description: Add a bot manager role. This allows members with this role to use features that are admin only.

subcommands.name: remove
subcommands.description: Remove a bot manager role.

subcommands.name: log
subcommands.description: Manage log settings.

subcommands.name: channel
subcommands.description: Set the channel where events will be logged to.

subcommands.name: add
subcommands.description: Add a log event. Valid events are user_verify, guild_sync, and bot_permission_error.

subcommands.name: remove
subcommands.description: Remove a log event.

subcommands.name: blacklist
subcommands.description: View or manage the application blacklist for this server.

subcommands.name: add
subcommands.description: Add a player to the blacklist. Reason will default to 'not provided' if not set.

subcommands.name: ban
subcommands.description: Add a player to the blacklist and ban them from the server. Reason will default to 'not provided' if not set.

subcommands.name: remove
subcommands.description: Remove a player from the blacklist.

subcommands.name: search
subcommands.description: Search for a player in the blacklist. Will show top five closest results.

subcommands.name: share
subcommands.description: Share your blacklist with another server.

subcommands.name: unshare
subcommands.description: Stop sharing your blacklist with another server.

subcommands.name: use
subcommands.description: Use a shared blacklist from another server.

subcommands.name: stop_using
subcommands.description: Stop using a shared blacklist from another server.

subcommands.name: enable
subcommands.description: Blacklisted people will not be able to use this feature. Feature can be verify or apply.

subcommands.name: disable
subcommands.description: Blacklisted people will be able to use this feature.

subcommands.secondDescription: Get a list of all the blacklisted players on this server with the reasons and NameMC links.

subcommands.name: jacob
subcommands.description: Main command for jacob event settings.

subcommands.name: enable
subcommands.description: Enable farming event notifications.

subcommands.name: disable
subcommands.description: Disable farming event notifications.

subcommands.name: channel
subcommands.description: Set the channel where farming event notifications will be posted.

subcommands.name: add
subcommands.description: Add a crop to be tracked and notified.

subcommands.name: remove
subcommands.description: Remove a crop from the tracking list.

subcommands.secondDescription: Get the current farming event settings for the bot.

subcommands.name: event
subcommands.description: Main command for event notification settings.

subcommands.name: enable
subcommands.description: Enable event notifications.

subcommands.name: disable
subcommands.description: Disable event notifications.

subcommands.name: add
subcommands.description: Add an event to be tracked and notified.

subcommands.name: remove
subcommands.description: Remove an event from the tracking list.

subcommands.secondDescription: Get the current event notification settings for the bot.

subcommands.name: verify
subcommands.description: Main command for verification settings.

subcommands.name: enable
subcommands.description: Enable automatic verify.

subcommands.name: disable
subcommands.description: Disable automatic verify.

subcommands.name: message
subcommands.description: The message that users will see when verifying.
examples: message Run /link <IGN> replacing IGN with your IGN to verify!

subcommands.name: roles
subcommands.description: Modify roles given on verification

subcommands.name: add
subcommands.description: Add a role that user will receive upon being verified. The role cannot be @everyone or a managed role. You can add a max of 5 roles.

subcommands.name: remove
subcommands.description: Remove a verify role.

subcommands.name: channel
subcommands.description: The channel where the verify message and verify button will be sent.

subcommands.name: nickname
subcommands.description:
The nickname template that a user will be renamed to on verifying. Can be set to none. Add .{text} for text that should only be added if the previous template was met. See example [here](https://discord.com/channels/796790757947867156/802749920679165994/937099157200580618).

You can use the following templates:
â€¢ [GUILD.NAME]
â€¢ [GUILD.TAG]
â€¢ [GUILD.RANK]
â€¢ [PLAYER.SKILLS]
â€¢ [PLAYER.CATACOMBS]
â€¢ [PLAYER.SLAYER]
â€¢ [PLAYER.WEIGHT]
â€¢ [PLAYER.CLASS]
â€¢ [PLAYER.LEVEL]
â€¢ [PLAYER.IRONMAN]
â€¢ [PLAYER.EMBLEM]

subcommands.name: remove_role
subcommands.description: Set the role that will be removed on verifying and re-added when un-verifying.

subcommands.name: sync
subcommands.description: Enable or disable verification automatic sync. This will sync the verified role(s) and nickname when a user joins the server or every hour (up to 160 members per sync).

subcommands.name: dm_on_join
subcommands.description: Enable or disable verification automatic DM on join sync. This will toggle if a user should be messaged when their roles are synced on joining the server.

subcommands.name: roles_claim
subcommands.description: Enable or disable automatic roles claim sync. This is the same as running the roles claim command on joining/linking/verifying.

subcommands.secondDescription: Get the current verification settings for the bot.

subcommands.name: roles
subcommands.description: Main command for automatic roles settings.

subcommands.name: enable
subcommands.description: Enable automatic roles.

subcommands.name: disable
subcommands.description: Disable automatic roles.

subcommands.name: add
subcommands.description: Add a new level to a role with its corresponding Discord role.

subcommands.name: remove
subcommands.description: Remove a role level for a role.

subcommands.name: use_highest
subcommands.description: Enable or disable using the highest values across all profile. Default is false

subcommands.name: sync
subcommands.description: Enable or disable automatic roles claim sync. This is the same as running `/roles claim` automatically every hour (up to 45 members will be updated per sync).

subcommands.secondDescription: Get the current roles settings for the bot.

subcommands.name: guild
subcommands.description: Main command for automatic guild (application and guild role/ranks).

subcommands.name: create
subcommands.description: Create a new automatic guild for a guild.

subcommands.name: remove
subcommands.description: Remove an automatic guild.

subcommands.name: member_role
subcommands.description: Automatic guild member role.

subcommands.name: enable
subcommands.description: Enable automatic guild role.

subcommands.name: disable
subcommands.description: Disable automatic guild role.

subcommands.name: role
subcommands.description: Set the role to give guild members.

subcommands.name: ranks
subcommands.description: Automatic guild ranks.

subcommands.name: enable
subcommands.description: Enable automatic guild ranks.

subcommands.name: disable
subcommands.description: Disable automatic guild ranks.

subcommands.name: add
subcommands.description: Add a guild rank.

subcommands.name: remove
subcommands.description: Remove a guild rank.

subcommands.name: counter
subcommands.description: Enable or disable the guild member counter. This will create the voice channel to display the current guild member count and updates every hour.

subcommands.name: apply
subcommands.description: Automatic application system for this guild.

subcommands.name: enable
subcommands.description: Enable automatic apply.

subcommands.name: disable
subcommands.description: Disable automatic apply.

subcommands.name: close
subcommands.description: Close automatic apply. Disables the button to create a new application.

subcommands.name: open
subcommands.description: Re-enable the button to create a new application.

subcommands.name: message
subcommands.description: The message that users will see when verifying.

subcommands.name: staff_roles
subcommands.description: Modify roles that will be pinged for an application

subcommands.name: add
subcommands.description: Add a role which will be pinged when a new application is submitted.

subcommands.name: remove
subcommands.description: Remove a staff ping role.

subcommands.name: channel
subcommands.description: Channel where the message to react for applying will sent.

subcommands.name: check_api
subcommands.description: Whether an applicant must have all APIs enabled in order to apply.

subcommands.name: category
subcommands.description: Category where new apply channels will be made. Run `categories` to get the ID's of all categories in the server.

subcommands.name: staff_channel
subcommands.description: Channel where new applications will be sent to be reviewed by staff.

subcommands.name: waiting_channel
subcommands.description: Channel where the players who were accepted or waitlisted will be sent. Optional and can be set to none.

subcommands.name: accept_message
subcommands.description: Message that will be sent if applicant is accepted.

subcommands.name: waitlist_message
subcommands.description: Message that will be sent if applicant is waitlisted. Optional and can be set to none.

subcommands.name: gamemode
subcommands.description: Whether applicants must use a certain gamemode profile in their application. Defaults to all. Options are: all, regular, ironman, stranded, or ironman_stranded.

subcommands.name: deny_message
subcommands.description: Message that will be sent if applicant is denied.

subcommands.name: requirements
subcommands.description: Requirements applications must meet. An application will be auto-denied if they do not meet the requirements.

subcommands.name: add
subcommands.description: Add a requirement that applicant must meet. Types are slayer, skills, catacombs, weight, lily_weight, level, networth, and farming_weight. At least one of the requirement types must be set.

subcommands.name: remove
subcommands.description: Remove a requirement by its index. Run `settings guild <name>` to see the index for all current requirements.

subcommands.name: scammer_check
subcommands.description: Enable or disable if a player should automatically be denied if they are marked as a scammer in the SkyblockZ database. Defaults to false.

secondDescription: View the current settings for this server.

name: setup
description: A guide on how to setup the bot.

name: categories
description: Get the ids of all categories in this server.

name: reload
description: Reload the automatic guild application(s) and automatic verification settings. This is required for most changes to take effect for both of these features.
